The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Avik parents visit Writers
                                                                                                                                     Avik parents visit Writers
            A STAFF REPORTER            Avik Chowdhury                           
	Calcutta: Parents of Avik Chowdhury  Sripati and Sushmita  Tuesday met officials at the chief ministers secretariat at Writers Buildings seeking help from the government for the treatment of the Bengal all-rounder.         
	Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee had visited Avik, who met with a car accident last month and is now recovering after a spinal surgery, when he was admitted in Ruby General Hospital.         
	We are grateful to the chief minister for visiting him. We came here to inform him about Aviks condition, Sripati Chowdhury said.         
	Avik, who is now medically stable, will be flown to Delhi for further treatment at the Indian Spinal Injuries Centre.         
	The treatment will come to around Rs 10 lakh, he added.         
	The day after the accident,the Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB), in a fine gesture, had announced to bear all of the cricketers medical expenses.                                                                                                                       
